## 2. Add deeper repetition and structure detection

Status: Complete for feature-artifact baseline; deeper parser inference can build on it.

- Done: current feature extraction detects run-lengths and repeated 2/3-byte
  n-grams.
- Done: family feature artifacts include wider repeated motifs for 4/5/6/8-byte
  subsequences under `motif_stats.wide_repeated_motifs`.
- Done: family feature artifacts include trailing data block and padding hints
  under `structure_stats.trailing_block_stats`.
- Done: family feature artifacts include fixed, mostly fixed, or variable length
  profiles under `structure_stats.length_profile`.
- Done: family feature artifacts include recurring fixed-position byte groups
  under `structure_stats.recurring_field_groups`.
- Done: these structure features are carried into `protocol_model.json` through
  family feature summaries and are available to the next LLM evidence exporter.
- Future enhancement: use these structure hints directly in boundary splitting
  and semantic labeling, not only as exported evidence.
